$AAPL &gt;&gt; look for $AAPL to test the middle Bollinger Band at 176.22 on the daily chart &gt;&gt;

If support breaks when tested the market could have a real dip &gt;&gt; 

$AAPL is too vertical off the Nov. 11 low at 148 &gt;&gt; 

Basically straight up from that level &gt;&gt; 

At some point in the near future I think $AAPL could end up retesting the 50 day simple moving average at 163.33 &gt;&gt; 

$AAPL pulled back to that level in September,  October &amp; November after trading above &gt;&gt;

This parabolic push with a nearly $3T market cap is unsustainable without some back filling &gt;&gt; 

On a dip to the 50 day simple moving average $AAPL would be a good buy if support held when tested &gt;&gt; 🤔
